=== Etymology ===
From the Latin ''[[libatio]]'' fr. ''[[libare]]'' "to take a little from anything, to taste, to pour out as an offering" 

=== Noun ===
'''libation'''
#
#* the act of [[pour]]ing a [[liquid]] or [[liquor]], usually [[wine]], either on the ground or on a [[victim]] in [[sacrifice]], in [[honor]] of some [[deity]]
#* the wine or liquid thus poured out
# a [[beverage]] especially an [[alcoholic]] one (often used humorously)

